&lt;p&gt;Renal Department Ward 124 based at Royal Stoke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, highly motivated Band 5 Nurse to work on Ward 124 within a busy Renal Department. The ward comprises of 28 beds which include 2 higher monitoring beds and 4 Assessment trolleys.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is cohesive and professional with a genuine interest and passion for providing a high standard of patient care. If you are looking for a new challenge, then this innovative unit will provide you with the opportunities for professional development and an exciting and rewarding career in Renal Nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Renal Unit is a new state of the art building and also includes a Haemodialysis Unit, Transplant Service, CKD team, Research Team and a Home Therapy Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Important Information:&lt;br /&gt;Please note the University Hospitals of North Midlands (NHS) Trust, do not pay travel expenses for candidates attending interviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSally AppletonJob titleSenior SisterEmail addresssally.appleton@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782 671792&lt;/p&gt;
